{"id":"ai-config-manager-leej","title":"Extract repo lock acquisition helper to reduce 8-site duplication","description":"## Problem

Eight cmd/ files contain the identical 7-line repo-lock block:

```go
repoLock, err := mgr.AcquireRepoLock(cmd.Context())
if err != nil {
    return fmt.Errorf("failed to acquire repository lock at %s: %w", mgr.RepoLockPath(), err)
}
defer func() {
    _ = repoLock.Unlock()
}()
```

Files: repo_add.go:161, repo_apply.go:74, repo_drop.go:57, repo_init.go:48, repo_remove.go:72, repo_sync.go:714, repo_repair.go:67, repo_verify.go:135, repo_prune.go:93.

Some use `mgr`, some `manager`; repo_verify uses different error variable name `lockErr`. But the logic is identical.

## Suggested fix

Add a helper in cmd/ (e.g. cmd/repo_helpers.go):

```go
func acquireRepoLock(ctx context.Context, mgr *repo.Manager) (*repolock.Lock, error) {
    lock, err := mgr.AcquireRepoLock(ctx)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to acquire repository lock at %s: %w", mgr.RepoLockPath(), err)
    }
    return lock, nil
}
```

Each call site becomes:
```go
repoLock, err := acquireRepoLock(cmd.Context(), mgr)
if err != nil { return err }
defer func() { _ = repoLock.Unlock() }()
```

This cuts 3 lines per call site (24 lines total) and centralizes the error message format. The defer stays at the call site because Go defer scoping requires it.

## Risk

Low — purely mechanical refactor. The test in repo_locking_test.go exercises the underlying AcquireRepoLock method and would catch any signature changes.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","owner":"hans.kohlreiter@dynatrace.com","created_at":"2026-03-19T18:44:00Z","created_by":"Hans Kohlreiter","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:44:00Z"}

{"id":"ai-config-manager-qy4s","title":"Extract test setup helper in repo_remove_test.go (16 duplicate setups)","description":"## Problem

cmd/repo_remove_test.go has 16 test functions that each repeat the same setup block:

\`\`\`go
tempDir := t.TempDir()
mgr := repo.NewManagerWithPath(tempDir)
if err := mgr.Init(); err != nil { t.Fatalf(...) }
manifest, err := repomanifest.Load(filepath.Join(tempDir, \"manifest.json\"))
// ... create source, add source, save ...
\`\`\`

The 16 instances are at lines: 23, 113, 157, 201, 274, 347, 371, 476, 582, 688, 745, 829, 943, 1004, 1080, 1155.

Each is ~12-15 lines of boilerplate. That is approximately 200+ lines of pure repetition.

## Suggested fix

Add a test helper at the top of the file:

\`\`\`go
func setupRemoveTestRepo(t *testing.T, sources ...repomanifest.Source) (*repo.Manager, *repomanifest.Manifest) {
    t.Helper()
    tempDir := t.TempDir()
    mgr := repo.NewManagerWithPath(tempDir)
    if err := mgr.Init(); err != nil {
        t.Fatalf(\"Init failed: %v\", err)
    }
    manifest, err := repomanifest.Load(filepath.Join(tempDir, \"manifest.json\"))
    if err != nil {
        t.Fatalf(\"Load manifest: %v\", err)
    }
    for _, src := range sources {
        manifest.AddSource(src)
    }
    if err := manifest.Save(); err != nil {
        t.Fatalf(\"Save manifest: %v\", err)
    }
    return mgr, manifest
}
\`\`\`

Each test shrinks from ~15 lines of setup to 1-3 lines.

## Risk

None — test-only change. Does not affect production code.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","owner":"hans.kohlreiter@dynatrace.com","created_at":"2026-03-19T18:45:02Z","created_by":"Hans Kohlreiter","updated_at":"2026-03-20T07:40:27Z","closed_at":"2026-03-20T07:40:27Z","close_reason":"Closed after queue review: not worth doing as standalone work"}

{"id":"ai-config-manager-c37b","title":"Remove double os.Stat call in addBulkFromLocalWithMode (repo_add.go:648-656)","description":"## Problem

cmd/repo_add.go lines 648-656 calls os.Stat(localPath) twice:

\`\`\`go
// Line 648 — checks existence
if _, err := os.Stat(localPath); err != nil {
    return fmt.Errorf("path does not exist: %s", localPath)
}

// Line 653 — gets file info for IsDir check
info, err := os.Stat(localPath)
if err != nil {
    return err
}
\`\`\`

The second call can never fail if the first succeeded (barring TOCTOU race, which isn't handled anyway). This is just two syscalls where one suffices.

## Suggested fix

\`\`\`go
info, err := os.Stat(localPath)
if err != nil {
    return fmt.Errorf("path does not exist: %s", localPath)
}
\`\`\`

Single call, same behavior, 4 fewer lines.

## Risk

None — trivially safe. The only behavioral difference is the error message for the second \`os.Stat\` failure case, which was unreachable anyway.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","owner":"hans.kohlreiter@dynatrace.com","created_at":"2026-03-19T18:44:54Z","created_by":"Hans Kohlreiter","updated_at":"2026-03-20T07:40:28Z","closed_at":"2026-03-20T07:40:28Z","close_reason":"Closed after queue review: not worth doing as standalone work"}

